  15 """*Experimental* support for running Keras models on the TPU.
  16 
  17 To use, wrap your model with the `keras_support.tpu_model` function.
  18 
  19 Example usage:
  20 
  21 ```
  22 image = tf.keras.layers.Input(shape=(28, 28, 3), name='image')
  23 c1 = tf.keras.layers.Conv2D(filters=16, kernel_size=(3, 3))( image)
  24 flattened = tf.keras.layers.Flatten()(c1)
  25 logits = tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')(flattened)
  26 model = tf.keras.Model(inputs=[image], outputs=[logits])
  27 
  28 resolver = tf.contrib.cluster_resolver.TPUClusterResolver(tpu=tpu_name)
  29 strategy = keras_support.TPUDistributionStrategy(resolver)
  30 model = keras_support.tpu_model(model, strategy=strategy)
  31 
  32 # Only TF optimizers are currently supported.
  33 model.compile(optimizer=tf.train.AdamOptimizer(), ...)
  34 
  35 # `images` and `labels` should be Numpy arrays.  Support for tensor input
  36 # (e.g. datasets) is planned.
  37 model.fit(images, labels)
  38 ```
  39 """
  40

  98 # TODO(b/114775106): temporary shim to optionally initialize the TPU
  99 # This increases the odds our session is initialized, but shouldn't be needed.
 100 _TEST_REWRITE_OP = None
 101 
 102 
 103 def _maybe_initialize_tpu(session):
 104   """Initialize the TPU if it has not already been initialized."""
 105   global _TEST_REWRITE_OP
 106   try:
 107     # Try to use cached version to avoid another ground of graph optimization.
 108     test_rewrite_op = _TEST_REWRITE_OP
 109     if (test_rewrite_op is None or
 110         test_rewrite_op[0].graph != ops.get_default_graph()):
 111 
 112       def test_op():
 113         return constant_op.constant(1) + constant_op.constant(1)
 114 
 115       test_rewrite_op = tpu.rewrite(test_op)
 116       _TEST_REWRITE_OP = test_rewrite_op
 117 
 118     session.run(test_rewrite_op)
 119   except errors.FailedPreconditionError as _:
 120     session.run(tpu.initialize_system())
 121 
 122 
 123 @contextlib.contextmanager
 124 def _tpu_session_context():
 125   """Initialize the TPU and cleans cache entries for bad sessions."""
 126   try:
 127     _maybe_initialize_tpu(K.get_session())
 128     yield
 129   except (errors.FailedPreconditionError, errors.AbortedError) as e:
 130     K.clear_session()
 131     raise Exception("""
 132 An error occurred connecting or initializing your TPU.
 133 
 134 The session has been reset. re-run keras_to_tpu_model to create a new session.
 135 """ + e)
 136

 138 def setup_tpu_session(cluster_resolver):
 139   """Construct or return a `tf.Session` connected to the given cluster."""
 140   master = cluster_resolver.master()
 141 
 142   # Use the existing session if we're already connected to this TPU
 143   # N.B K.get_session() is a non-trivial operation, and may fail if the remote
 144   # session has been reset.
 145   try:
 146     default_session = K.get_session()
 147     if (default_session._target == master and
 148         getattr(default_session, '_tpu_initialized', None)):
 149       return
 150   except errors.AbortedError as _:
 151     # We lost the remote session and need to re-initialize.
 152     logging.warning('Lost remote session: creating a new session.')
 153 
 154   cluster_spec = cluster_resolver.cluster_spec()
 155   config = config_pb2.ConfigProto(isolate_session_state=True)
 156   if cluster_spec:
 157     config.cluster_def.CopyFrom(cluster_spec.as_cluster_def())
 158 
 159   tpu_session = tf_session.Session(target=master, config=config)
 160   tpu_session.run(tpu.initialize_system())
 161   tpu_session._tpu_initialized = True
 162 
 163   # N.B. We have to call `K.set_session()` AND set our session as the
 164   # TF default. `K.get_session()` surprisingly does not return the value
 165   # supplied by K.set_session otherwise.
 166   K.set_session(tpu_session)
 167

 175 def get_tpu_system_metadata(tpu_cluster_resolver):
 176   """Retrieves TPU system metadata given a TPUClusterResolver."""
 177   master = tpu_cluster_resolver.master()
 178 
 179   # pylint: disable=protected-access
 180   cluster_spec = tpu_cluster_resolver.cluster_spec()
 181   cluster_def = cluster_spec.as_cluster_def() if cluster_spec else None
 182   tpu_system_metadata = (
 183       tpu_system_metadata_lib._query_tpu_system_metadata(
 184           master, cluster_def=cluster_def, query_topology=False))
 185 
 186   return tpu_system_metadata

 189 class TPUDistributionStrategy(object):
 190   """The strategy to run Keras model on TPU."""
 191 
 192   def __init__(self, tpu_cluster_resolver=None, using_single_core=False):
 193     """Construct a TPUDistributionStrategy.
 194 
 195     Args:
 196       tpu_cluster_resolver: Any instance of `TPUClusterResolver`. If None, will
 197         create one with '' as master address.
 198       using_single_core: Bool. This is the debugging option, which might be
 199         removed in future once the model replication functionality is mature
 200         enough. If `False` (default behavior), the system automatically finds
 201         the best configuration, in terms of number of TPU cores, for the model
 202         replication, typically using all avaiable TPU cores. If overwrites as
 203         `True`, force the model replication using single core, i.e., no
 204         replication.
 205     Raises:
 206       Exception: No TPU Found on the given worker.
 207     """
 208 
 209     if tpu_cluster_resolver is None:
 210       tpu_cluster_resolver = tpu_cluster_resolver_lib.TPUClusterResolver('')
 211 
 212     metadata = get_tpu_system_metadata(tpu_cluster_resolver)
 213     self._tpu_metadata = metadata
 214     self._tpu_cluster_resolver = tpu_cluster_resolver
 215     self._num_cores = 1 if using_single_core else metadata.num_cores
 216 
 217     # Walk device list to identify TPU worker for enqueue/dequeue operations.
 218     worker_re = re.compile('/job:([^/]+)')
 219     for device in metadata.devices:
 220       if 'TPU:0' in device.name:
 221         self._worker_name = worker_re.search(device.name).group(1)
 222         return
 223     raise Exception('No TPU found on given worker.')
 224 
 225   def _make_assignment_for_model(self, cpu_model):
 226     """Makes a `TPUAssignment` for the passed in `cpu_model`."""
 227     num_cores = self._num_cores
 228     if num_cores > 1 and cpu_model.stateful:
 229       logging.warning(
 230           'Model replication does not currently support stateful models.  '
 231           'Degrading to a single core.')
 232       num_cores = 1
 233 
 234     return TPUAssignment(worker_name=self._worker_name, num_cores=num_cores)
 235 
 236 
 237 class TPUAssignment(object):
 238   """This is object holding TPU resources assignment for the concrete model.
 239 
 240   `TPUDistributionStrategy` is responsible to create the instance of
 241   `TPUAssignment`, so, it can dynamically adjust the `num_cores` to use based on
 242   model and input batch sizes.
 243   """
 244 
 245   def __init__(self, worker_name, num_cores):
 246     self._worker_name = worker_name
 247     self._num_cores = num_cores
 248 
 249   @property
 250   def worker_name(self):
 251     return self._worker_name
 252 
 253   @property
 254   def num_towers(self):
 255     # TODO(xiejw): Support automatically assign num_cores based on inputs.
 256     return self._num_cores

 259 class TPUEmbedding(embeddings.Embedding):
 260   """TPU compatible embedding layer.
 261 
 262   The default Keras layer is not TPU compatible.  This layer is a drop-in
 263   replacement: it has the same behavior and will work on CPU and GPU devices.
 264   """
 265 
 266   def build(self, input_shape):
 267     if input_shape[0] is None:
 268       raise ValueError(
 269           'TPUEmbeddings must have a fixed input_length or input shape.')
 270     return super(TPUEmbedding, self).build(input_shape)
 271 
 272   def call(self, inputs):
 273     if K.dtype(inputs) != 'int32':
 274       inputs = math_ops.cast(inputs, 'int32')
 275 
 276     inputs = array_ops.one_hot(inputs, self.input_dim)
 277     return math_ops.tensordot(inputs, self.embeddings, 1)
 278

 280 def _cross_replica_concat(tensor, core_id, num_cores, name):
 281   """Concatenate `tensor` across cores.
 282 
 283   Args:
 284     tensor: The tensor to be concatenated. Must be [int32 and float32].
 285     core_id: Tensor indicating the current TPU core.
 286     num_cores: Python int. The total number of TPU cores in the system.
 287     name: The string name to print for debugging.
 288 
 289   Returns:
 290     The same concatenated Tensor on each core.
 291   """
 292 
 293   input_dtype = tensor.dtype
 294   if input_dtype not in [dtypes.float32, dtypes.int32]:
 295     raise TypeError('For model replication, only (float32 and int32) is '
 296                     'supported for model outputs and targets. Got {} for '
 297                     '{}.'.format(input_dtype, name))
 298 
 299   batch_size = tensor.shape[0]
 300   mask = math_ops.to_float(
 301       math_ops.equal(np.arange(num_cores, dtype=np.int32), core_id))
 302   mask = array_ops.reshape(mask, [num_cores] + [1] * tensor.shape.ndims)
 303   result = mask * math_ops.to_float(tensor)
 304   local_tensor_with_holes = array_ops.reshape(result,
 305                                               [-1] + result.shape.as_list()[2:])
 306   concat_tensor = tpu_ops.cross_replica_sum(local_tensor_with_holes)
 307   concat_tensor.set_shape((num_cores * batch_size,) + tuple(tensor.shape[1:]))
 308 
 309   if concat_tensor != input_dtype:
 310     concat_tensor = math_ops.cast(concat_tensor, input_dtype)
 311   return concat_tensor

 314 class KerasCrossShardOptimizer(keras_optimizers.Optimizer):
 315   """An optimizer that averages gradients across TPU shards."""
 316 
 317   def __init__(self, opt, name='KerasCrossShardOptimizer'):
 318     """Construct a new cross-shard optimizer.
 319 
 320     Args:
 321       opt: An existing `Optimizer` to encapsulate.
 322       name: Optional name prefix for the operations created when applying
 323         gradients. Defaults to "KerasCrossShardOptimizer".
 324 
 325     Raises:
 326       ValueError: If reduction is not a valid cross-shard reduction.
 327     """
 328     super(KerasCrossShardOptimizer, self).__init__()
 329     self._name = name
 330     self._opt = opt
 331     logging.info('KerasCrossShard: %s %s', self._opt, self._opt.weights)
 332 
 333   def get_updates(self, loss, params):
 334     self._opt.get_gradients = self.get_gradients
 335     return self._opt.get_updates(loss, params)
 336 
 337   def get_gradients(self, loss, params):
 338     num_shards = tpu_function.get_tpu_context().number_of_shards
 339     grads = super(KerasCrossShardOptimizer, self).get_gradients(loss, params)
 340     return [tpu_ops.cross_replica_sum(grad) / num_shards for grad in grads]
 341 
 342   def get_weights(self):
 343     return self._opt.get_weights()
 344 
 345   def get_config(self):
 346     return self._opt.get_config()
 347 
 348   # Defer remaining operations to the underlying optimizer
 349   def __getattr__(self, key):
 350     return getattr(self._opt, key)
 351

 360 def _valid_name(tensor_name):
 361   """Return a valid tensor name (strips '/', ':', etc)."""
 362   return re.sub('[^a-zA-Z0-9_-]+', '', tensor_name)

 364 
 365 def _replicated_optimizer(opt):
 366   """Wrap the optimizer `opt` with CrossShardOptimizer if applicable."""
 367   # Always wrap `opt` with CrossShardOptimizer, even if we are running on a
 368   # single core.  This ensures Keras properly tracks and initializes optimizer
 369   # variables.
 370   if isinstance(opt, keras_optimizers.TFOptimizer):
 371     return tpu_optimizer.CrossShardOptimizer(opt.optimizer)
 372   else:
 373     return KerasCrossShardOptimizer(opt)
 374 
 375 
 376 def _clone_optimizer(optimizer, config=None):
 377   """Returns a cloned optimizer with the provided optimizer.config or config."""
 378   if not isinstance(optimizer, keras_optimizers.Optimizer):
 379     # In the first call to tpu_model(model), Keras may not have wrapped the TF
 380     # optimizer in the TFOptimizer helper, e.g., the given model isn't compiled
 381     # or optimizer isn't set, and later generated tpu_model compiles with a TF
 382     # optimizer.
 383     return optimizer
 384 
 385   if isinstance(optimizer, keras_optimizers.TFOptimizer):
 386     return keras_optimizers.TFOptimizer(optimizer.optimizer)
 387 
 388   if config is None:
 389     config = optimizer.get_config()
 390   logging.info('Cloning %s %s', optimizer.__class__.__name__, config)
 391   return optimizer.__class__.from_config(config)

 394 class TPURewriteContext(object):
 395   """Prepare the environment for a Keras model during `tpu.rewrite`.
 396 
 397   This overrides the default placeholder behaviour to instead refer to a preset
 398   input mapping.  Placeholders are unsupported in TPU compiled code, and must
 399   be replaced with explicit inputs or values from the infeed queue.
 400 
 401   Instead of explicitly threading inputs all the way through the Keras codebase,
 402   we override the behavior of the placeholder while compiling and inject the
 403   Tensors from the infeed in place of the placeholder.
 404 
 405   Similarly, as we compile a new sub-graph for each unique shape and execution
 406   mode, we need to override the behavior of an embedded `name_scope` call in
 407   the base Keras layer code.  This allows us to re-use the same weights across
 408   many compiles and share a single session/graph.
 409   """
 410 
 411   def __init__(self, input_map):
 412     self._input_map = input_map
 413     self._default_placeholder = None
 414     self._default_name_scope = None
 415 
 416   def __enter__(self):
 417 
 418     def _placeholder(dtype, shape=None, name=None):  # pylint: disable=unused-argument
 419       logging.info('Remapping placeholder for %s', name)
 420       if name in self._input_map:
 421         return self._input_map[name]
 422       else:
 423         logging.info('Default: %s', name)
 424         return self._default_placeholder(dtype, shape, name)
 425 
 426     def _name_scope(name, default_name=None, values=None):
 427       caller_frame = sys._getframe().f_back
 428       caller_obj = caller_frame.f_locals.get('self')
 429       if (caller_obj is not None and
 430           isinstance(caller_obj, base_layer.Layer) and name is not None):
 431         return variable_scope.variable_scope(
 432             name, default_name, values, reuse=variable_scope.AUTO_REUSE)
 433 
 434       return self._default_name_scope(name, default_name, values)
 435 
 436     self._default_placeholder = array_ops.placeholder
 437     self._default_name_scope = ops.name_scope
 438     self._default_make_variable = base_layer.make_variable
 439     self._default_random_normal = random_ops.random_normal
 440     self._default_qr = gen_linalg_ops.qr
 441 
 442     array_ops.placeholder = _placeholder
 443 
 444     # Replace random_ops.random_normal with a dummy function because
 445     # `random_normal` isn't yet implemented on the TPU. Because these
 446     # initialized values are overwritten by the CPU values, this is okay.
 447     def random_normal(shape,
 448                       mean=0.0,
 449                       stddev=1.0,
 450                       dtype=dtypes.float32,
 451                       seed=None,
 452                       name=None):
 453       del mean
 454       del stddev
 455       del seed
 456       return array_ops.zeros(shape, dtype=dtype, name=name)
 457 
 458     random_ops.random_normal = random_normal
 459 
 460     # Replace gen_linalg_ops.qr because QR decomposition is not yet implemented.
 461     # TODO(saeta): Remove qr override once we confirm the qr implementation is
 462     # ok.
 463     # pylint: disable=redefined-builtin
 464     def qr(input, full_matrices=False, name=None):
 465       """Dummy implementation of qr decomposition."""
 466       del full_matrices  # TODO(saeta): Properly handle the full matrix case.
 467       input_shape = input.shape
 468       if len(input_shape) < 2:
 469         raise ValueError('Invalid shape passed to qr: %s' % input_shape)
 470       p = min(input_shape[-1], input_shape[-2])
 471       if len(input_shape) == 2:
 472         q = array_ops.zeros((p, p), name=name)
 473         r = array_ops.zeros(input_shape, name=name)
 474         return (r, q)
 475       elif len(input_shape) == 3:
 476         n = input_shape[0]
 477         q = array_ops.zeros((n, p, p), name=name)
 478         r = array_ops.zeros(input_shape, name=name)
 479         return (r, q)
 480       else:
 481         raise ValueError('Invalid shape passed to qr: %s' % input_shape)
 482 
 483     gen_linalg_ops.qr = qr
 484 
 485     ops.name_scope = _name_scope
 486     base_layer.make_variable = variable_scope.get_variable
 487     logging.info('Overriding default placeholder.')
 488     return
 489 
 490   def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb):
 491     array_ops.placeholder = self._default_placeholder
 492     ops.name_scope = self._default_name_scope
 493     base_layer.make_variable = self._default_make_variable
 494     random_ops.random_normal = self._default_random_normal
 495     gen_linalg_ops.qr = self._default_qr
 496
